	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=19194&mid=104631140275851>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=19194&mid=104631140275851>RE: Balanced...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=19194&mid=104631140275851#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Feb 26th 9:35 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=86947><span id=Guru>Annheiser</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>170 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.32]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Damage bonus is added to every successful hit from your primary hand weapon. Off-hand weapons do not get damage bonuses. So if you were to normally hit for 20, a damage bonus of 7 would net you 27 damage instead. <br><br>Two-Handed weapons generally have better damage bonuses because they take into account the delay of the weapon along with other variables. One-handers have lower damage bonuses since they only take into consideration your level.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb 27 11:33:42 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>**********************************<br>"<span style='color: red;'>Man who goes to bed with itchy bum, wakes with smelly fingers.</span style='color: red;'>"</td></tr>
